{
	"VersionNumber": 1,
	"ResourceName": "fortinet_protocols",
	"Description": "This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet protocols. It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.\n\nfields:\nproto_id,protocol,proto_state,state,description,expiry_timer\n  - proto_id: this is the protocol id for the event\n  - proto: this is the protocol name for the event\n  - proto_state: this is the protocol state for the event\n  - state: this is the protocol state name for the event\n  - description: this is more information about the priority for the event\n  - expiry_timer: this is the default expiry timer for that protocol and state\n\nReference(s):\n  - Fortinet \n    - https://community.fortinet.com/t5/FortiGate/Troubleshooting-Tip-FortiGate-session-table-information/ta-p/196988\n\nUsage: lookup -r fortinet_protocols proto_id proto (proto_id protocol proto_state state description expiry_timer)",
	"Labels": [
		"fortinet"
	],
